Here are both approaches for .NET MAUI Shell navigation:

**1. The Product model**

```csharp
public class Product
{
    public string Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public decimal Price { get; set; }
}
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage (code-behind or VM)**

```csharp
// Approach A – pass a simple string ID
async Task GoToDetailsWithId(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(
        $"{nameof(ProductDetailsPage)}?productId={product.Id}");
}

// Approach B – pass the full object via dictionary
async Task GoToDetailsWithObject(Product product)
{
    var parameters = new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        { "product", product }   // object passed by reference, not serialized
    };

    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), parameters);
}
```

**3. Register the route (in AppShell.xaml.cs)**

```csharp
Routing.RegisterRoute(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**4. ProductDetailsViewModel – receive both with IQueryAttributable**

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private Product _product;

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A – simple string parameter
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var idObj))
        {
            string productId = idObj.ToString();
            // Load product from a service / database
            LoadProduct(productId);
        }

        // Approach B – full object
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var productObj) && productObj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
        }
    }

    private async void LoadProduct(string id)
    {
        Product = await SomeService.GetProductAsync(id);
    }
}
```

**5. Wire the VM to the page**

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | String param (`?key=val`) | Object param (dictionary) |
|---|---|---|
| **Serialization** | URL-encoded string only | Passed by reference, any type |
| **Deep-link / URI support** | ✅ works in URIs | ❌ only programmatic nav |
| **Use when** | Simple IDs, small values | Complex objects already in memory |

> **Tip:** `ApplyQueryAttributes` is called *before* the page appears, so bindings resolve in time. If you need both approaches on the same page, just handle both keys in the same method as shown above.
